    {
      "type": "teach",
      "title": "Tall and deep letters",
      "body": "Many Shavian consonants come in pairs: a tall letter for an unvoiced sound, and a deep letter for its voiced twin. Say “ffff”, then “vvvv” — feel your throat buzz on the second one? That buzz is voicing. Tall letters rise above the line; deep letters hang below it — a handy reminder, since your vocal cords sit low when they buzz."
    },
